verses.text_plain: Praise ye the Lord: for it is good to sing praises unto our God; for it is pleasant; and praise is comely.
verses.verse_html: 1Praise ye the Lord: for it is good to sing praises unto our God; for it is pleasant; and praise is comely.

verses.text_plain: The Lord doth build up Jerusalem: he gathereth together the outcasts of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 2The Lord doth build up Jerusalem: he gathereth together the outcasts of Israel.

verses.text_plain: He healeth the broken in heart, and bindeth up their wounds.
verses.verse_html:
3He healeth the broken in heart, and bindeth up their wounds. ▼
▼ wounds: Heb. griefs

verses.text_plain: He telleth the number of the stars; he calleth them all by their names.
verses.verse_html: 4He telleth the number of the stars; he calleth them all by their names.

verses.text_plain: Great is our Lord, and of great power: his understanding is infinite.
verses.verse_html:
5Great is our Lord, and of great power: his understanding is infinite. ▼
▼ his…: Heb. of his understanding there is no number

footnotes.body_text: ▼ his…: Heb. of his understanding there is no number
footnotes.body_html: ▼ his…: Heb. of his understanding there is no number

verses.text_plain: The Lord lifteth up the meek: he casteth the wicked down to the ground.
verses.verse_html: 6The Lord lifteth up the meek: he casteth the wicked down to the ground.

verses.text_plain: Sing unto the Lord with thanksgiving; sing praise upon the harp unto our God:
verses.verse_html: 7Sing unto the Lord with thanksgiving; sing praise upon the harp unto our God:

verses.text_plain: Who covereth the heaven with clouds, who prepareth rain for the earth, who maketh grass to grow upon the mountains.
verses.verse_html: 8Who covereth the heaven with clouds, who prepareth rain for the earth, who maketh grass to grow upon the mountains.

verses.text_plain: He giveth to the beast his food, and to the young ravens which cry.
verses.verse_html: 9He giveth to the beast his food, and to the young ravens which cry.

verses.text_plain: He delighteth not in the strength of the horse: he taketh not pleasure in the legs of a man.
verses.verse_html: 10He delighteth not in the strength of the horse: he taketh not pleasure in the legs of a man.

verses.text_plain: The Lord taketh pleasure in them that fear him, in those that hope in his mercy.
verses.verse_html: 11The Lord taketh pleasure in them that fear him, in those that hope in his mercy.

verses.text_plain: Praise the Lord, O Jerusalem; praise thy God, O Zion.
verses.verse_html: 12Praise the Lord, O Jerusalem; praise thy God, O Zion.

verses.text_plain: For he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates; he hath blessed thy children within thee.
verses.verse_html: 13For he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates; he hath blessed thy children within thee.

verses.text_plain: He maketh peace in thy borders, and filleth thee with the finest of the wheat.
verses.verse_html:
14He maketh peace in thy borders, and filleth thee with the finest of the wheat. ▼
▼ He…: Heb. Who maketh thy border peace
 , ▼
▼ finest…: Heb. fat of wheat

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He…: Heb. Who maketh thy border peace
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He…: Heb. Who maketh thy border peace
▼ finest…: Heb. fat of wheat

verses.text_plain: He sendeth forth his commandment upon earth: his word runneth very swiftly.
verses.verse_html: 15He sendeth forth his commandment upon earth: his word runneth very swiftly.

verses.text_plain: He giveth snow like wool: he scattereth the hoarfrost like ashes.
verses.verse_html: 16He giveth snow like wool: he scattereth the hoarfrost like ashes.

verses.text_plain: He casteth forth his ice like morsels: who can stand before his cold?
verses.verse_html: 17He casteth forth his ice like morsels: who can stand before his cold?

verses.text_plain: He sendeth out his word, and melteth them: he causeth his wind to blow, and the waters flow.
verses.verse_html: 18He sendeth out his word, and melteth them: he causeth his wind to blow, and the waters flow.

verses.text_plain: He sheweth his word unto Jacob, his statutes and his judgments unto Israel.
verses.verse_html:
19He sheweth his word unto Jacob, his statutes and his judgments unto Israel. ▼
▼ his word: Heb. his words

footnotes.body_html: ▼ his word: Heb. his words

verses.text_plain: He hath not dealt so with any nation: and as for his judgments, they have not known them. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 20He hath not dealt so with any nation: and as for his judgments, they have not known them. Praise ye the Lord.
